def: Reproof; censure; blame; disapproval.This Basilius took as though his mistress had given him a secretreprehension that he had not showed more gratefulness to Dorus. SirP. Sidney.
A genus of bitter herbs or shrubs having eight stamens and atwo-celled ovary (as the Seneca snakeroot, the flowering wintergreen,etc.); milkwort.
A cap of cells which covers the growing extremity of a root; arootcap.
In fives; consisting of five in one; five repeated; quintuple.
An inferior magistrate or judge among the Mohammedans, usuallythe judge of a town or village.
Of, like, composed of, containing, nummulites; as, nummuliticbeds.
One whose occupation is to manufacture utensils, ornaments,etc., of silver; a worker in silver.
Accused by one's self or by one's conscience. "Die self-accused." Cowper.
Tight; stretched; not slack; -- said esp. of a rope that istightly strained.
Lady; a lady; -- a title formerly given to noble ladies whoheld a barony in their own right. Burrill.
The bean or seed of the castor-oil plant (Ricinus communis, orPalma Christi.)
